Awesome. I dropped a ready-to-paste “Start Your Project” section in the canvas. It’s a single HTML file you can add to a GoDaddy HTML block (or host on a subdomain). It includes four cards, a modal that opens your forms/scheduler/visualizer in place, and basic GA4 events.

What you’ll replace (copy/paste from canvas, then edit these)

https://tally.so/r/REPLACE_WITH_SPECIALIST_FORM → your Talk to a Specialist form URL

https://tally.so/r/REPLACE_WITH_QUICK_QUOTE_FORM → your Quick Quote multi-step form URL

https://tally.so/r/REPLACE_WITH_DESIGNER_FORM → your Designer Intake form URL

https://calendly.com/REPLACE_CALENDLY/intro → your Calendly booking link

https://example.com/your-planner and /your-visualizer → your DIY tools (or just link out)

If you don’t have form links yet, use any of these (all allow file upload and webhooks to HubSpot/QuickBooks/Slack):

Tally (fast, clean multi-step), Jotform, or HubSpot Forms (if using HubSpot CRM).

Field lists & choices (use these in your forms)

Lead basics (required ✱)

First name✱, Last name✱, Email✱, Phone (optional), Contact preference (Email / Phone)

Quick Quote qualifiers

Budget band: <$5k, $5–10k, $10–15k, $15–25k, $25–40k, $40k+

Timeline: ASAP (<30 days), 1–2 months, 3–4 months, 5–6 months, 6+ months

Project type: Kitchen, Bath, Laundry, Closet, Other

Door style: Shaker, Slim Shaker, Raised Panel, Slab, Other

Finish color: White, Gray, Blue, Black, Natural/Wood, Other

Notes (long text)

File upload (PDF/JPG/PNG up to 20–25 MB) — layout, sketches, inspiration

Designer service intake

Service tier: Free (up to 2 revisions; 48–72h) / Premium (faster + extras)

Rooms count / scope

Are you a contractor or property manager? Yes/No

Shipping ZIP (for lead routing)

Marketing consent checkbox + link to your Privacy Policy

Events you’ll get out-of-the-box

The snippet fires start_project.open with {title, src} when a user opens any card’s modal. If you paste your GA4 gtag code on the page, you’ll see these immediately. You can add more (e.g., on form submit) later.

How to add this to GoDaddy (Website Builder)

Go to your Start Your Project page → Add Section → HTML.

Paste everything from the canvas file into that block.

Replace the placeholder links above.

Publish.
